# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics in the Angular application following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to the project dependencies
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependencies

### 2. Added Analytics Scripts to HTML
Modified: `src/index.html`
- Added the Vercel Web Analytics tracking script initialization in the `<head>` section
- Added the deferred script tag that loads the Vercel insights script from `/_vercel/insights/script.js`
- These scripts will automatically track page views and visitors once the app is deployed to Vercel

## Implementation Details

For Angular applications without a specific framework integration, I used the HTML/plain JavaScript approach as recommended in the Vercel documentation:

```html
<script>
  window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js"></script>
```

This implementation:
- Initializes the global `window.va` function for analytics tracking
- Loads the Vercel insights script asynchronously with the `defer` attribute
- Will automatically start tracking once the app is deployed to Vercel with Web Analytics enabled

## Build Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ Analytics scripts are properly included in the generated HTML output
- ✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality

## Next Steps

To complete the Web Analytics setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Visit the deployed site to verify tracking is working (check for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view` in browser DevTools)
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab

## Notes

- The `@vercel/analytics` package was installed but the HTML approach was used for integration as it's the recommended method for frameworks without specific Vercel Analytics components
- No route support is available with this implementation method (route tracking requires framework-specific integrations)
- The tracking will only activate when deployed on Vercel with Web Analytics enabled
